<subSubSection id="C3C4BB9BA6522C0FFF17F9A911EFF90D" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B61E810A6522C0FFF17F9A911CCF92E" blockId="45.[151,1437,1615,2036]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName id="4CDE9393A6522C0FFF17F9A91162F992" box="[151,263,1615,1640]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponerinae">Ponerinae</taxonomicName>
is the largest ant subfamily outside the formicoid clade, and is rivaled or exceeded in diversity only by 
<taxonomicName id="4CDE9393A6522C0FFF17F9951122F976" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1878" box="[151,327,1651,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dolichoderinae">Dolichoderinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4CDE9393A6522C0FFED2F99511B7F976" box="[338,466,1651,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Formicinae">Formicinae</taxonomicName>
and Myrmicinae within that clade. The tribal and generic organization of 
<taxonomicName id="4CDE9393A6522C0FFA92F99515E7F976" box="[1298,1410,1651,1676]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ponerinae">Ponerinae</taxonomicName>
is here revised to reflect new molecular phylogenetic results (
<bibRefCitation id="EF4F95E1A6522C0FFCE2F9711475F94A" author="Schmidt, C." box="[866,1040,1687,1712]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="201 - 250" refId="ref161753" refString="Schmidt, C. (2013) Molecular phylogenetics of ponerine ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae: Ponerinae). Zootaxa, 3647 (2), 201 - 250. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3647.2.1" type="journal article" year="2013">Schmidt, 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and a reassessment of ponerine morphological diversity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B61E810A6522C0FFF47F93911EFF90D" blockId="45.[151,1437,1615,2036]" box="[199,394,1759,1784]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B9AA3402A6522C0FFF47F93911E1F902" bold="true" box="[199,388,1759,1784]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Included Tribes</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
